results.occurrenceRemarks: According to  NZ birds on line this bird is the Antipodean albatross sub-species Gibson's (Diomedea antipodensis gibsoni). But other authorities seem to agree with Naturewatch by classifying this bird as a sub species of wandering albatross (Diomedea exulans gibsoni). Either way it was a magnificent bird to observe.
